                                <li>Info session about what is going on/ planned for New Cross & Deptford</li>
                                <li>Specific developments and potential impact, using local planning information, and a case study of a development. </li>
                                <li>Effect of government welfare reforms on social housing, such as social exclusion, social cleansing</li>
                                <li>Right-To-Buy and how it will affect London social housing</li>
                                <li>Affordable Housing (80% market), & being priced out of the city</li>
                            </ul>
                            [1hour, 1pm – 2pm, Main Tent]
                        </li>
                        <li class="tcmb"><em class="text-muted3">The Solution/ Ways to Organise/ Combating the “Inevitable”:</em> Investigating methods to combat these problems, using the knowledge of existing groups in the Social and Alternative housing sectors:</li>
                        <span class="text-muted3">Social Housing </span>(incl Housing Associations, co-ops, council housing): how to challenge the threat to social housing, eg right-to-buy, evictions, “affordable” rents. Panel delegates from various housing action groups.
                    <span style="display: block;" class="tcmb">[1 hour, 3pm – 4pm, Main Tent]</span>
                        <li class="tcmb"><em class="text-muted3">Workshops:</em> workshops will look at practical ways to organise and resist social cleansing. Breakout into <em class="text-muted3">FOUR workshops </em>around tent city, to include:
                            <ul>
                                <li>Tenant Empowerment: Tenant-led management, and tenant participation in HA strategy and policy making </li>
                                <li>Organising a Housing Action Group</li>
                                <li>Squatting and Eviction Resistance</li>
                                <li>Benefits Advice</li>
                            </ul>
